meanings.definition: Past participle of outstrive: to surpass in striving or effort.
meanings.sent1: She had outstriven all her classmates in the race.
meanings.sent2: He outstriven his own record in the weightlifting competition.
meanings.sent3: The little ant outstriven the big grasshopper in gathering food.
meanings.sent4: Her determination outstriven any obstacle in her path.
meanings.sent5: The sun outstriven the clouds, shining brightly in the sky.
